==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pucka
<hw>Puck"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>pukka</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Hind. <ets>pakk⟦amac⟧</ets> cooked,
ripe, solid.]</ety> <def>Good of its kind; -- variously used as implying
substantial, real, fixed, sure, etc., and specif., of buildings, made of
brick and mortar.</def> <mark>[India]</mark></p>

<p><q>It's <qex>pukka</qex> famine, by the looks of it.</q>
<rj><qau>Kipling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puckball</ent>⟦br⟧
